    <div class="section" id="home">
        <h2>Welcome to Global Outreach Youth Organization</h2>
        <p>#reaching all posibilities</p>
        <p>We empower youth to make positive changes in their communities.</p>
        <p>Our mission is clear: to empower the next generation with economic opportunities, essential skills training, and invaluable insights into the world of technology and artificial intelligence (AI). We believe that by equipping young minds with these tools, we can break the cycle of poverty, unleash their full potential, and pave the way for a brighter future.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section" id="about">
            <h2>About Us</h2>
            <p>Global Outreach Youth Organization is a beacon of hope for the youth in rural areas, particularly situated in the heart of Moetagare Ga Matlala, a village nestled in the picturesque landscapes of Limpopo, South Africa.</p>
            <p>Our mission is clear: to empower the next generation with economic opportunities, essential skills training, and invaluable insights into the world of technology and artificial intelligence (AI). We believe that by equipping young minds with these tools, we can break the cycle of poverty, unleash their full potential, and pave the way for a brighter future.</p>
            <p>Founded by visionary leaders deeply rooted in the local community, our organization is driven by a passion for change and a commitment to uplift the marginalized. We understand the challenges faced by rural youth - the lack of resources, limited access to education, and the daunting prospect of unemployment. That's why we're dedicated to bridging these gaps and providing pathways to success.</p>
            <p>At Global Outreach Youth Organization, we don't just offer handouts; we provide hand-ups. Through our comprehensive programs, we offer practical skills training in various fields, mentorship opportunities, and access to innovative technologies. We believe in nurturing talent, fostering entrepreneurship, and instilling confidence in the leaders of tomorrow.</p>
            <p>Join us on this transformative journey as we strive to create a world where every young person has the chance to thrive, regardless of their background or circumstances. Together, we can unlock the boundless potential within every individual and build a brighter, more inclusive future for all.</p>
        </div>
        
    </div>

    <div class="section" id="programs">
        <h2>Our Programs</h2>
        <p>Explore our various programs designed to help youth develop their skills and passions.</p>
        <div class="project-section" id="project1">
            <h2>NYDA BMT 27 MAY 2024</h2>
            <p>Business Management Training
                “Providing entrepreneurial skills to young people”
                
                What is the Business Management Training Programme?
                
                The Entrepreneurship Development Programme is aimed at creating a conducive environment for young entrepreneurs to access relevant entrepreneurship skills, knowledge, values and attitudes for their businesses.</p>
                <p>The programme offers entrepreneurship trainings that responds appropriately and adequately to the market and business needs of the young people.</p>
                <p>The Business Management Training courses is designed to support young entrepreneurs in the following stages of the businesses:

                    • Pre-start Up/Idea generation
                    
                    • Survivalist
                    
                    • Start Up
                    
                    • Early Development
                    
                    • Growth & Expansion</p>
                    <p>The Business Management Training courses on offer are approved and accredited by ILO, The International Labour Organisation. Start and Improve Your Business (SIYB) is the largest global business management training programme. It assists small scale entrepreneurs to start and grow their businesses and create employment. These training courses are offered as a 3-6 day training course depending on the specific needs of the young person and the level of the business. They are :

                        • GYBI – Generate Your Business Idea
                        
                        • SYB – Start Your Business
                        
                        • IYB – Improve Your Business</p>
                        <p>1. GENERATE YOUR BUSINESS IDEA – GYBI

                            Objective: This course enables potential entrepreneurs to develop a concrete business idea
                            
                            - Course Duration: 3 days
                            
                            
                            
                            Modules covered on the course:
                            
                            Part I - You are an Entrepreneur
                            
                            Part II - A market is waiting for you
                            
                            Part III - Your own Business Idea List
                            
                            Part IV - The best Business Idea for You
                            
                            Part V - Your own Business Idea
                            
                             
                            
                            <p>Participant Certificate: Participants will receive a “Certificates of Completion” for the 3 day GYBI training course completed - on the on the last day of the training
                            
                             
                            
                            2. START YOUR BUSINESS – SYB
                            
                            Objective: This course enables potential entrepreneurs to develop a bankable business plan and enhance their skills and knowledge.
                            
                            Course Duration:  5 days training + 1 day Pitching
                            
                             
                            
                            Modules covered on the course: 5 days
                            
                            Part I - Assess Your Readiness to a Start a Business
                            
                            Part II - The Business Plan
                            
                            Part III - Reinforce Your Business Idea
                            
                            Part IV - The Marketing Plan
                            
                            Part V - Staff
                            
                            Part VI - Organisation and Management
                            
                            Part VII - Buying for your Business
                            
                            Part VIII - Greening Your Business
                            
                            Part IX - Costing Your Goods & Services
                            
                            Part X - Financial Panning
                            
                            Part XI - Required Start Up Capital
                            
                            Part XII - Types and Sources of Start Up Capital
                            
                            Part XIII - Starting the Business
                            
                             
                            
                            Post Training – Pitching Session:  1 day
                            
                            • Pitching session is mandatory – where the participants make presentations post the SYB training
                            
                             
                            
                            Participant Certificate: Certificates are issued only at the pitching session</p>
                            
                            <p>3. IMPROVE YOUR BUSINESS - IYB
                            
                            Objective: This course enables existing entrepreneurs to develop their skills and improvement plans for their business
                            
                            Course Content and Duration: 
                            
                            IYB content is divided into 2 courses :
                            
                            • IYB Course 1 : 5 training days + 1 Pitching 
                            
                            • IYB Course 2 : 5 training days + 1 Pitching</p> 
                            
                            
                            
                           <p> 3.1 IYB Course 1  (5 days)
                            
                            • Marketing
                            
                            • Buying and Stock Control
                            
                            • People and Productivity</p>
                            
                             
                            
                            <p>3.2 IYB Course 2  (5 days)
                            
                            • Costings
                            
                            • Record Keeping
                            
                            • Planning for your Business</p>
                            
                             
                            
                           <p> Post Training – Pitching Session : 1 day
                            
                            • Pitching session is mandatory – where the participants make presentations post the IYB training</p>
                            
                             
                            
                           <p> Who is Eligible for Business Management Training?
                            
                            • South African citizens, between the ages of 18 and 35
                            
                            • With a valid South African Identity document
                            
                            • The business must be 100% youth owned
                            
                            • Young entrepreneurs wanting to access a grant or voucher and do not meet the requirement of the programme</p>
                            
                             
                            
                            <p>What is the process of applying for accessing the Business Management Training?
                            
                            • Visit the closest NYDA branch. See list of branches here
                            
                            • Submit the training application form and all other required documents to the nearest NYDA branch
                            
                            • A desk assessment is conducted by the branch
                            
                            • If approved, the participant will be provided with the following
                            
                            o Notification of the approved training course
                            
                            o logistics for the Training
                            
                            o logistics for the Pitching Session
                            
                            •The participant must present their  South African Identity Document at the first day of the training
                            
                            • Participants attending the SYB and IYB courses will also be required to attend a mandatory  “Pitching Session” on a date scheduled by the branch.
                            
                            • Participants will be issued with a “Certificate of Completion” for participating in the NYDA Training course</p>
        </div>
    
